  "prompt": "Which best and cheap badminton racket should I buy?",
  "response": "When looking for a budget-friendly yet quality badminton racket, there are several options you can consider. Here are a few recommendations that balance performance and affordability:\n\n1. **Yonex Muscle Power 2**: This racket offers good control and decent power for beginners. It's lightweight and well-balanced, making it a favorite among new players.\n\n2. **Li-Ning Windstorm 78**: Known for its lightweight design, this racket offers good maneuverability and is suitable for beginners to intermediate players. It's known for its durable construction.\n\n3. **Victor Brave Sword 190**: This is another great option for those looking for an affordable racket. It provides a good balance of power and control, making it suitable for casual play.\n\n4. **Apacs EdgeSaber 10**: Apacs is known for producing quality rackets at reasonable prices. The EdgeSaber 10 is lightweight and designed for players who enjoy fast gameplay.\n\n5. **Babolat I Pulse Lite**: A lightweight racket that offers good power and control. It's a solid choice for recreational players and those just starting out.\n\nWhen choosing a racket, consider factors like your playing style (defensive, offensive), grip size, and the balance of the racket (head-heavy vs. head-light). You may also want to visit a local sports store to try out different rackets to see what feels comfortable for you. Prices can vary, so keep an eye out for promotions or discounts to get the best deal.",
